            "prompt": "Create the following file at `/Users/jopcmelo/Developer/resend/react-email/packages/editor/src/bubble-menu/node-selector.tsx`.\n\nThis is for the `@react-email/editor` package. An unstyled compound component for selecting block types (paragraph, headings, lists, etc.) in a bubble menu.\n\n**Dependencies available:** `@tiptap/react` (`useCurrentEditor`, `useEditorState`), `react`. **NO Radix UI, NO icon library.** All styling via data-attributes and className props.\n\n### Architecture\n\nThe NodeSelector is a compound component with these parts:\n\n1. **`NodeSelector`** — The root wrapper. Uses React context to share state between children.\n   Props:\n   - `children: React.ReactNode`\n   - `className?: string`\n   \n   Internally manages `open` state (boolean). Provides context: `{ open, setOpen, activeItem, items, editor }`.\n\n2. **`NodeSelectorTrigger`** — The button that toggles the dropdown.\n   Props:\n   - `className?: string`\n   - `children?: React.ReactNode` — if provided, renders custom children. Otherwise renders `{activeItemName} <ChevronSvg />`.\n   \n   Renders `<button data-part=\"node-selector-trigger\" data-state={open ? 'open' : 'closed'}>`.\n\n3. **`NodeSelectorContent`** — The dropdown content container.\n   Props:\n   - `className?: string`\n   - `children?: React.ReactNode` — if provided, renders custom children. Otherwise renders default items.\n   \n   Only renders when `open` is true. Renders `<div data-part=\"node-selector-content\">`.\n\n4. **`NodeSelectorItem`** — Individual item in the dropdown.\n   Props:\n   - `name: string` — must match a known block type\n   - `icon?: React.ComponentType<{ className?: string }>` — optional custom icon\n   - `className?: string`\n   - `children?: React.ReactNode` — if provided, renders custom children\n   \n   Renders `<button data-part=\"node-selector-item\" data-active={isCurrentlyActive || undefined}>`.\n\n### Default Items\n\nThe selector knows about these block types (same as dashboard):\n```ts\ntype NodeSelectorItemConfig = {\n  name: string;\n  command: (editor: Editor) => void;\n  isActive: (editor: Editor) => boolean;\n};\n\nconst DEFAULT_ITEMS: NodeSelectorItemConfig[] = [\n  { name: 'Text', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleNode('paragraph', 'paragraph').run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('paragraph') && !ed.isActive('bulletList') && !ed.isActive('orderedList') },\n  { name: 'Title', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleHeading({ level: 1 }).run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('heading', { level: 1 }) },\n  { name: 'Subtitle', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleHeading({ level: 2 }).run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('heading', { level: 2 }) },\n  { name: 'Heading', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleHeading({ level: 3 }).run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('heading', { level: 3 }) },\n  { name: 'Bullet List', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleBulletList().run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('bulletList') },\n  { name: 'Numbered List', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleOrderedList().run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('orderedList') },\n  { name: 'Quote', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleNode('paragraph', 'paragraph').toggleBlockquote().run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('blockquote') },\n  { name: 'Code', command: (ed) => ed.chain().focus().clearNodes().toggleCodeBlock().run(), isActive: (ed) => ed.isActive('codeBlock') },\n];\n```\n\n### Context\n\nCreate a `NodeSelectorContext` using `React.createContext`. The context holds:\n```ts\ninterface NodeSelectorContextValue {\n  open: boolean;\n  setOpen: (state: boolean) => void;\n  activeItemName: string;\n  items: NodeSelectorItemConfig[];\n  editor: Editor;\n}\n```\n\n### Inline SVG\n\nCreate a small chevron-down SVG component (not exported) used in the default trigger.\n\n### Key behaviors:\n- When an item is clicked, it runs