            "prompt": "Create the following file at `/Users/jopcmelo/Developer/resend/react-email/packages/editor/src/bubble-menu/link-form.tsx`.\n\nThis is for the `@react-email/editor` package. An unstyled compound component for editing links in a bubble menu. This is the OSS version — no Resend-specific dependencies (no toast, no variables dropdown, no VARIABLE_PATTERN).\n\n**Dependencies available:** `@tiptap/react` (`useCurrentEditor`, `useEditorState`), `react`.\n\n### Architecture\n\nThe LinkForm is a compound component:\n\n1. **`LinkForm`** — The root form element. Manages link editing state.\n   Props:\n   - `element?: 'link' | 'button' | 'image'` — what type of element's href to edit. Default `'link'`.\n   - `validateUrl?: (url: string) => string | null | undefined` — custom URL validator. Returns normalized URL string on success, `null`/`undefined` on failure. Default: built-in validator that prepends `https://` for dot-containing strings.\n   - `onError?: (message: string) => void` — called when validation fails.\n   - `onSubmit?: (url: string) => void` — called after successful submission.\n   - `onUnlink?: () => void` — called after unlinking.\n   - `className?: string`\n   - `children?: React.ReactNode` — if provided, renders custom children. Otherwise renders default form layout.\n   \n   Renders `<form data-part=\"link-form\" onSubmit={handleSubmit}>`.\n   \n   Provides context: `{ inputRef, inputValue, setInputValue, hasLink, currentHref, handleSubmit, handleUnlink, element }`.\n\n2. **`LinkFormInput`** — The URL text input.\n   Props:\n   - `className?: string`\n   - `placeholder?: string` — default `'Paste a link'`\n   \n   Renders `<input data-part=\"link-form-input\" ref={inputRef from context} value={inputValue} onChange={...} />`.\n   Auto-focuses on mount.\n\n3. **`LinkFormSubmit`** — Submit button. Only shown when there's no existing link.\n   Props:\n   - `className?: string`\n   - `children?: React.ReactNode` — default renders a check SVG