e, Uppercase\n- Filters out items in `exclude`\n- Appends `extra` items with their active states resolved\n\n#### 3. `useAlignmentItems`\n\nSame pattern as `useFormattingItems` but for alignment.\n\n```ts\ninterface UseAlignmentItemsOptions {\n  exclude?: string[];\n}\n```\n\nReturns items for: Align Left, Align Center, Align Right.\n\n#### 4. `useNodeSelectorItems`\n\nReturns node selector item configs.\n\n```ts\ninterface UseNodeSelectorItemsOptions {\n  exclude?: string[];\n}\n```\n\nReturns items for: Text, Title, Subtitle, Heading, Bullet List, Numbered List, Quote, Code.\nEach item has `name`, `isActive` (boolean from useEditorState), `command`.\nAlso returns `activeItemName: string` (the currently active item, or 'Multiple').\n\n#### 5. `useLinkForm`\n\nExtracts link form logic.\n\n```ts\ninterface UseLinkFormOptions {\n  element?: 'link' | 'button' | 'image';\n  validateUrl?: (url: string) => string | null | undefined;\n  onError?: (message: string) => void;\n}\n\ninterface UseLinkFormReturn {\n  inputRef: React.RefObject<HTMLInputElement | null>;\n  inputValue: string;\n  setInputValue: (value: string) => void;\n  hasLink: boolean;\n  currentHref: string;\n  handleSubmit: (e?: React.FormEvent) => void;\n  handleUnlink: (e?: React.MouseEvent) => void;\n}\n```\n\nImplementation:\n- Uses `useCurrentEditor()` and `useEditorState()` to read current href\n- Manages input state with `useState`\n- Input ref for focusing\n- Auto-focuses input on mount via `useEffect`\n- `handleSubmit`: validates URL, sets href on editor, calls onError on failure\n- `handleUnlink`: clears href on editor\n\nThe `setHref` helper is internal:\n```ts\nfunction setHref(editor: Editor, element: string, href: string) {\n  if (element === 'button') { editor.commands.updateAttributes('button', { href }); return; }\n  if (element === 'image') { editor.commands.updateAttributes('image', { href }); return; }\n  if (href.length === 0) { editor.chain().unsetLink().run(); return; }\n  const { from,